    "Name": "Watchman WTC-4MB",
    "Details": "Debuted in 3144 on the Hartford Gardens Arena and piloted by Penny O'Hara, Watchman Belle is an experiment in bringing master-and-drone technology into the realm of BattleMech dueling. This 'Mech features a type of modified command console that allows a copilot to control a heavyweight drone — a Vulpes refit nicknamed the Beast. 'Mech armament is completely changed, with a quartet of ER medium lasers that support a single Large Re-Engineered Laser. This combination of firepower taxes the ’Mech’s twelve Double Heat Sinks. Seven tons of ferro-fibrous armor protect the 'Mech. The 'Mech adds a Clan Watchdog System electronics package. This effective blend of active probe and ECM hardware not only allows Belle to disrupt her adversaries’ sensors, but also serves as a powerful counter-countermeasures suite, that can punch through hostile interference that might otherwise render her Beast a very expensive and impotent statue.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Easy to Pilot</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.04</color></b>",
    "Icon": "Watchman"
  },
